# Context & handoff

**Framework:** `$FRAMEWORK_ROOT/INSTRUCTIONS.md` · **Data:** `$MEMORY_HOME` (`<install>/memory/`)

## When to read what

| Question | Skill | File |
|----------|-------|------|
| Who am I / my projects | `global-context` | `$MEMORY_HOME/context/GLOBAL_CONTEXT.md` |
| Where we stopped | `agent-handoff` | `<repo>/AGENT_HANDOFF.md` |
| What we discussed before | `chat-memory` | `$MEMORY_HOME/chats/projects/<slug>.md` |
| What worked / failed | `feedback-memory` | `$MEMORY_HOME/feedback/` + `preferences.md` |

**Do not load all layers every session.** Flow E (proposing) → feedback first.

## Session start (default)

1. If `<repo>/AGENT_HANDOFF.md` exists → read it first (Flow A in INSTRUCTIONS.md)
2. Add `global-context` only if project unclear or conventions/infra needed
3. Add `chat-memory` only if user needs past decisions

## Session end

1. Read `~/.cursor/hooks/agent-memory-session.log` if present (see `agent-memory-session-end.mdc`)
2. Update handoff · conventions · **semantic-merge** staging → Decisions
3. `verify-memory.py` · optional `distill-merge --apply` (Recent only)

Skills: `bash "$FRAMEWORK_ROOT/scripts/link-cursor-skills.sh"`
